WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:03.003
[ Click, static crackling ]
Check. Check. Is it good?

00:03.003 --> 00:05.297
Okay. Thanks.

00:05.297 --> 00:07.382
I don't want to knock
the light.

00:07.382 --> 00:08.634
[ Clears throat ]

00:08.634 --> 00:10.344
This here good?
Interviewer: That's great.

00:10.344 --> 00:11.762
Alright.

00:11.762 --> 00:13.680
Uh, when my son Henry
was born,

00:13.680 --> 00:15.807
he had
a, uh, heart condition ‐‐

00:15.807 --> 00:17.643
uh, Tetralogy of Fallot.

00:17.643 --> 00:20.896
Um, it's actually a combination
of four heart defects

00:20.896 --> 00:23.649
that are, uh, fatal, uh,
without surgery.

00:23.649 --> 00:25.317
Multiple surgeries.

00:25.317 --> 00:29.446
And...to watch your child
go through that,

00:29.446 --> 00:32.491
it was...a tough time.

00:32.491 --> 00:37.079
But one thing
that always cheered my family up

00:37.079 --> 00:38.121
was the show "Paul's Place."

00:38.121 --> 00:40.916
[ Up‐tempo music plays ]

00:40.916 --> 00:43.669
♪♪

00:43.669 --> 00:45.796
[ Audience gasps, laughs ]

00:45.796 --> 00:47.923
Mmm! Tastes good!

00:47.923 --> 00:50.092
[ Laughter, applause ]

00:50.092 --> 00:51.718
The star of the show,
the boy who played Paul,

00:51.718 --> 00:52.886
was Corey Harris.

00:52.886 --> 00:54.972
He was so funny.

00:54.972 --> 00:56.848
Henry would do
the milkshake thing,

00:56.848 --> 00:58.016
you know,
pretending to be Corey.

00:58.016 --> 00:59.351
"Mmm!
Tastes so good!"

00:59.351 --> 01:01.937
And he would make such a mess,
but...

01:01.937 --> 01:03.480
how could you be mad?

01:03.480 --> 01:06.608
I always said to myself
if I ever met him,

01:06.608 --> 01:08.193
I would thank him.

01:08.193 --> 01:09.486
You know,
just shake his hand.

01:12.197 --> 01:14.283
That was before I found out
what he'd become.

01:14.283 --> 01:16.910
Corey: I am
the Prophet Jedediah.

01:16.910 --> 01:19.246
And tomorrow,
the 3rd of June,

01:19.246 --> 01:22.291
is the day that we, the Worthy,
shall ascend.

01:22.291 --> 01:23.500
Aurora: The time for questions
is done.

01:23.500 --> 01:24.418
...get the hell out of my class
right now!

01:24.418 --> 01:25.586
Robin Roberts: ...drugs,
alcohol...

01:25.586 --> 01:26.920
Corey: I'm scared!
I don't want to die!

01:26.920 --> 01:28.714
[ Thud, gunshot ]
Aah!

01:28.714 --> 01:30.757
Nolan: I just couldn't believe
what happened

01:30.757 --> 01:34.511
to that sweet kid that my son
looked up to, you know?

01:34.511 --> 01:36.638
I couldn't believe
that I was there for all of it.

01:36.638 --> 01:42.144
♪♪

01:42.144 --> 01:47.858
♪♪

01:47.858 --> 01:49.401
[ Mouse clicks, music stops ]

01:49.401 --> 01:51.945
Jackson: Sorry.
I'm just a little nervous.

01:51.945 --> 01:53.697
That's ‐‐ I'm assuming
that's normal, yeah?

01:53.697 --> 01:55.073
Interviewer: Oh, totally.
But there's no pressure.

01:55.073 --> 01:56.992
We're just talking.
Okay.

01:56.992 --> 01:58.452
Uh, where ‐‐
where should I start?

01:58.452 --> 01:59.619
Tell me about June 3rd.

01:59.619 --> 02:02.289
Yeah. It started off
like any other day.

02:02.289 --> 02:04.291
A few mundane calls.

02:04.291 --> 02:07.085
And then the world
went crazy.

02:07.085 --> 02:09.963
Los Angeles was thrown
into chaos today

02:09.963 --> 02:12.507
when the Emergency Alert System
inadvertently sent out

02:12.507 --> 02:14.301
a text message stating

02:14.301 --> 02:17.262
a nuclear missile
was headed for the city.

02:17.262 --> 02:19.139
It felt like
the end of the world.

02:19.139 --> 02:20.766
We helped as many people
as we could

02:20.766 --> 02:23.352
and then headed for shelter.

02:23.352 --> 02:25.937
That's when we saw them,
standing on the ledge,

02:25.937 --> 02:29.483
20 stories up,
waiting for their...

02:29.483 --> 02:30.525
How do I put it?

02:30.525 --> 02:33.403
Their ride, uh, from the aliens.

02:33.403 --> 02:37.866
Turned out there was this dude
named the Prophet Jedediah

02:37.866 --> 02:40.661
who told them that on June 3rd,

02:40.661 --> 02:43.872
E.T. was coming
to embrace his followers

02:43.872 --> 02:46.249
during their...ascension.

02:46.249 --> 02:48.460
Group: All hail Children
of the Stars.

02:48.460 --> 02:50.045
Lopez: And for the first time
in history, a cult leader

02:50.045 --> 02:52.172
actually guessed the right date
for the apocalypse.

02:52.172 --> 02:54.508
Turns out this prophet
had been predicting for years

02:54.508 --> 02:57.636
that June 3, 2019, would be
the date for their ascension.

02:57.636 --> 02:58.762
And it was just dumb luck

02:58.762 --> 03:00.889
that the missile alert happened
that day.

03:00.889 --> 03:02.683
I mean, these people
were so brainwashed

03:02.683 --> 03:04.351
that they were gonna jump
to their death.

03:04.351 --> 03:06.978
Thank God
that Officer Lopez was there.

03:06.978 --> 03:09.356
I mean, she saved
all of their lives.

03:09.356 --> 03:10.982
You got to understand,
we had no idea

03:10.982 --> 03:13.443
who this Prophet Jedediah was.

03:13.443 --> 03:15.612
And in the crazy days
that followed,

03:15.612 --> 03:18.156
he kind of fell
through the cracks.

03:18.156 --> 03:21.451
Not that it would've made
any difference if...

03:21.451 --> 03:23.578
Well, at least I don't think
it would've.

03:23.578 --> 03:25.288
Dispatch: <i>7‐Adam‐15,</i>
<i>possible 207,</i>

03:25.288 --> 03:26.873
<i>9901 Violet Drive.</i>

03:26.873 --> 03:28.208
<i>RP is on scene.</i>

03:28.208 --> 03:29.709
Benjamin: ...my daughter
out here!

03:29.709 --> 03:30.752
[ Knock on door ]

03:30.752 --> 03:32.546
Oh, good. The cops.

03:32.546 --> 03:34.297
Debbie!

03:34.297 --> 03:36.633
Look, my daughter
is inside this house.

03:36.633 --> 03:38.260
He's keeping her.

03:38.260 --> 03:39.594
He won't let her leave.

03:39.594 --> 03:41.179
He's brainwashing her.

03:41.179 --> 03:42.347
Good morning, Officers.
I'm so sorry

03:42.347 --> 03:43.515
you had to be bothered
with this.

03:43.515 --> 03:45.142
I know you.
You're Corey Harris.

03:45.142 --> 03:46.059
You're from that, uh...

03:46.059 --> 03:47.018
"Paul's Place."

03:47.018 --> 03:49.062
Yeah.
That was a lifetime ago,

03:49.062 --> 03:50.939
but it's always nice
to meet a fan.

03:50.939 --> 03:51.648
You want an autograph?

03:51.648 --> 03:53.692
It threw me.

03:53.692 --> 03:56.361
Uh, the thing about celebrities
is I think

03:56.361 --> 03:59.489
they get locked in time
in your head, you know?

03:59.489 --> 04:01.491
Whatever that show is
you loved them from,

04:01.491 --> 04:04.327
that's the way
you always expect them to be.

04:04.327 --> 04:05.620
Corey Harris had done
some other shows

04:05.620 --> 04:07.372
since "Paul's Place"
but nothing that stuck.

04:07.372 --> 04:09.082
You know, people called him
a child star,

04:09.082 --> 04:10.292
as if that was
some kind of failing.

04:10.292 --> 04:12.169
But even so, I, um ‐‐

04:12.169 --> 04:13.795
I was definitely
a little starstruck.

04:13.795 --> 04:17.090
I mean, it didn't really matter
to me that he was famous.

04:17.090 --> 04:18.758
I mean, this is L. A.

04:18.758 --> 04:22.137
Every other house is owned
by a superstar or a model

04:22.137 --> 04:24.222
or...cult leader.

04:24.222 --> 04:25.974
Will you arrest him?

04:25.974 --> 04:28.018
He's keeping my daughter
against her will.

04:28.018 --> 04:29.811
He ‐‐ He's a cult leader!

04:29.811 --> 04:31.438
It's not a cult.

04:31.438 --> 04:34.733
It's a religious movement ‐‐
awaiting tax‐exempt status.

04:34.733 --> 04:36.026
Aurora is over 18
and here of her own volition.

04:36.026 --> 04:37.736
Her name is Debbie.

04:37.736 --> 04:40.030
Aurora has shed
her birth name,

04:40.030 --> 04:42.073
like a moth
becoming a butterfly.

04:42.073 --> 04:43.825
Caterpillar.

04:43.825 --> 04:45.202
Moths don't become
butterflies.

04:45.202 --> 04:47.162
Uh, can we speak
to Debbie, please?

04:47.162 --> 04:48.371
Of course.

04:48.371 --> 04:49.790
Aurora!

04:49.790 --> 04:51.583
[ Birds chirping ]

04:51.583 --> 04:53.752
Yes, Prophet?

04:53.752 --> 04:54.795
Can you tell
these nice officers

04:54.795 --> 04:56.129
that you're here
of your own free will?

04:56.129 --> 04:58.298
I'm here
of my own free will.

04:58.298 --> 04:59.633
Harper: Oh, that was
convincing.

04:59.633 --> 05:01.551
Debbie, please.
This is crazy.

05:01.551 --> 05:02.803
You got to come home.

05:02.803 --> 05:04.805
I <i>am</i> home.

05:04.805 --> 05:06.473
You got to stop her.
Why don't you wait inside
while we talk to Debbie?

05:06.473 --> 05:08.141
Harper: I can't, sir.
She's an adult.

05:08.141 --> 05:09.309
Only if that's what
Aurora wants.

05:09.309 --> 05:10.393
I have nothing else
to say.

05:10.393 --> 05:11.394
I'm happy here,
with my real family.

05:11.394 --> 05:12.562
But, D‐Debbie ‐‐

05:12.562 --> 05:14.981
Debbie, your mother's cancer ‐‐
It's back!

05:14.981 --> 05:16.358
She's dying!

05:16.358 --> 05:18.026
She's only got a couple weeks
to live!

05:18.026 --> 05:19.778
[ Breathing heavily ]

05:19.778 --> 05:22.739
She needs you.

05:22.739 --> 05:24.199
Corey: Aurora?

05:24.199 --> 05:29.830
♪♪

05:29.830 --> 05:32.207
[ Exhales sharply ]

05:32.207 --> 05:33.834
Harper: It was like
a switch flipped.

05:33.834 --> 05:35.710
Aurora w‐‐ Um, not Aurora.

05:35.710 --> 05:38.171
Uh, Debbie went back inside,

05:38.171 --> 05:39.548
and she packed
all of her stuff

05:39.548 --> 05:42.217
and then she left
with her dad.

05:42.217 --> 05:44.344
I guess she just needed
a cold, hard dose

05:44.344 --> 05:45.720
of reality
to bring her back.

05:45.720 --> 05:47.514
Interviewer: You said earlier
you wanted to thank Corey

05:47.514 --> 05:49.766
for helping you and your son,
shake his hand.

05:49.766 --> 05:51.434
Did you?
No. No.

05:51.434 --> 05:54.145
It felt, um, super inappropriate
at the time.

05:54.145 --> 05:56.231
So we just headed out,

05:56.231 --> 05:57.691
and I thought
that was the end of it.

06:02.863 --> 06:05.031
[ Tires squeal ]

06:05.031 --> 06:09.744
♪♪

06:09.744 --> 06:10.871
Tim:
You the one who called?

06:10.871 --> 06:13.123
Yes.
I garden for Mr. Harris.

06:13.123 --> 06:14.749
I found blood
by the door.

06:14.749 --> 06:15.959
Lucy: Did you go
in the home?

06:15.959 --> 06:17.836
No.
Okay. Go wait over
by your truck.

06:17.836 --> 06:19.462
We'll check it out and come back
and get your statement.

06:19.462 --> 06:20.589
Thank you.

06:20.589 --> 06:24.634
♪♪

06:24.634 --> 06:25.760
Police!

06:25.760 --> 06:27.304
Mr. Harris, are you home?

06:27.304 --> 06:28.847
Lucy: Control, 7‐Adam‐19,
we've got blood

06:28.847 --> 06:31.683
at 9901 Violet Drive.

06:31.683 --> 06:33.143
We're gonna clear
the house.

06:33.143 --> 06:34.936
Notify supervisor,
request additional units.

06:34.936 --> 06:36.646
[ Hinges squeaking ]

06:36.646 --> 06:40.108
♪♪

06:40.108 --> 06:41.860
Blood.

06:41.860 --> 06:47.449
♪♪

06:47.449 --> 06:52.829
♪♪

06:52.829 --> 06:53.830
Lucy: Tim.

06:53.830 --> 06:58.043
♪♪

06:58.043 --> 06:59.669
We have major blood loss
at our location.

06:59.669 --> 07:01.421
Send detectives
and TID.

07:03.423 --> 07:05.008
[ Sniffs ]
Is this gonna take long?

07:05.008 --> 07:07.385
Because, uh,
we got work to do.

07:07.385 --> 07:08.845
Interviewer: Um...uh,
what can you tell me

07:08.845 --> 07:10.972
about the crime scene?

07:10.972 --> 07:12.515
Well, I mean,
that amount of blood,

07:12.515 --> 07:15.268
if it came from one person,
then that's fatal.

07:15.268 --> 07:16.686
Without Corey's body,
we had to treat it

07:16.686 --> 07:19.147
as a missing‐persons case
while the lab ran the blood

07:19.147 --> 07:20.649
against Corey's DNA.

07:20.649 --> 07:21.816
But no one was home?

07:21.816 --> 07:23.026
We didn't know that yet.

07:23.026 --> 07:24.527
We hadn't cleared
the house.

07:24.527 --> 07:27.614
It ‐‐ Corey's disciples
were at a drum circle downtown.

07:27.614 --> 07:30.075
They did it once a week
to recruit new followers.

07:30.075 --> 07:31.284
Yeah. The house's
security camera

07:31.284 --> 07:32.619
captured them all leaving
right before ‐‐

07:32.619 --> 07:34.371
Oh, yeah.
We have a video of them

07:34.371 --> 07:35.705
downtown
across from City Hall.

07:35.705 --> 07:37.666
I'm sorry. I cut you off.
I'm sorry.

07:37.666 --> 07:40.794
I was just gonna say that
the security system

07:40.794 --> 07:43.171
was shut off
right after they all left.

07:43.171 --> 07:44.714
It took three hours
to reboot.

07:44.714 --> 07:48.093
So there's no video
of the crime.

07:48.093 --> 07:49.177
[ Whispering ]
This is fun.

07:49.177 --> 07:50.470
Benjamin:
What is this about?

07:50.470 --> 07:51.680
Look, I need to be
at the hospital.

07:51.680 --> 07:52.972
My wife doesn't
have much time left.

07:52.972 --> 07:54.349
We understand, sir.

07:54.349 --> 07:56.309
Uh, you can take a seat,
please.

07:56.309 --> 07:58.353
We will try
and make this quick.

07:58.353 --> 07:59.646
[ Exhales deeply ]

07:59.646 --> 08:02.857
Were you at the hospital
yesterday?

08:02.857 --> 08:04.150
All day and night.

08:04.150 --> 08:05.777
Was your daughter there
with you?

08:05.777 --> 08:08.446
What do you think?

08:08.446 --> 08:12.367
She hasn't seen her dying mother
in years because of that man.

08:12.367 --> 08:15.036
D‐Do you understand the whiplash
that Debbie's experienced

08:15.036 --> 08:18.331
in the last two days alone?

08:18.331 --> 08:21.418
Seeing her mother again
has j‐‐ opened her eyes

08:21.418 --> 08:23.586
to everything that she has been
missing in the world ‐‐

08:23.586 --> 08:24.963
all the love,
all the joy

08:24.963 --> 08:29.217
that Corey has withheld from her
all of this time.

08:29.217 --> 08:32.053
Corey went missing
yesterday.

08:32.053 --> 08:35.849
There were signs of violence
at his house.

08:35.849 --> 08:38.560
Good.

08:38.560 --> 08:44.983
He destroyed our family,
destroyed Debbie's life.

08:44.983 --> 08:48.528
[ Sighs ]

08:48.528 --> 08:51.322
It was just supposed to be
an acting class.

08:51.322 --> 08:52.699
You think the most
important quality

08:52.699 --> 08:54.492
of a great actor
is talent?

08:54.492 --> 08:56.077
Wrong!

08:56.077 --> 08:58.455
It's the ability
to be mercenary,

08:58.455 --> 09:00.373
to do whatever it takes
to get a part

09:00.373 --> 09:03.501
and to use that role
to get the next one.

09:03.501 --> 09:05.670
Trust me. I'm living proof
of what happens when you don't.

09:05.670 --> 09:07.505
So when the acting jobs
dried up,

09:07.505 --> 09:09.299
Corey started
an acting school.

09:09.299 --> 09:13.011
And he basically just used it
to air his grievances

09:13.011 --> 09:14.387
about Hollywood...

09:14.387 --> 09:16.014
After "Paul's Place,"
I just assumed

09:16.014 --> 09:17.807
that the starring roles would
keep coming, but they didn't.

09:17.807 --> 09:20.560
...and to convince
these kids that, you know,

09:20.560 --> 09:21.895
he was the only one
that could help them

09:21.895 --> 09:24.481
navigate this evil world.

09:24.481 --> 09:26.858
I'm not here
to teach you methods.

09:26.858 --> 09:27.984
I'm here to teach you that
unless you're willing

09:27.984 --> 09:30.236
to cross every line

09:30.236 --> 09:32.280
and throw every inhibition
you have out the window,

09:32.280 --> 09:34.783
then you should get the hell
out of my class right now!

09:36.743 --> 09:39.579
But...if you stay,

09:39.579 --> 09:41.956
I will help you.

09:41.956 --> 09:44.042
I will nurture you.

09:44.042 --> 09:46.252
I will give you a safe place
to become a star.

09:46.252 --> 09:47.754
Harper:
And these twenty‐somethings,

09:47.754 --> 09:49.172
they fell for it,

09:49.172 --> 09:52.675
and they paid thousands
of dollars for these classes

09:52.675 --> 09:55.887
that slowly just turned
into pseudo‐religious

09:55.887 --> 09:57.972
character‐building seminars.

09:57.972 --> 09:59.432
Nolan: He made them
feel special.

09:59.432 --> 10:01.101
You know, in a business
that makes people

10:01.101 --> 10:03.353
feel like garbage
on a regular basis,

10:03.353 --> 10:04.938
it wasn't long before Debbie
and the others

10:04.938 --> 10:08.775
started treating him
like a...a guru.

10:08.775 --> 10:11.361
You know, he literally told them
how to act,

10:11.361 --> 10:13.947
and in their eyes,
he became infallible.

10:13.947 --> 10:15.782
He could do no wrong.

10:15.782 --> 10:18.243
He could commit acts
of unspeakable evil

10:18.243 --> 10:20.453
yet still be their savior
from above.

10:20.453 --> 10:22.831
I can't speak
to Officer Nolan's comments,

10:22.831 --> 10:24.833
but what we discovered
at Corey's house that day

10:24.833 --> 10:27.836
was pretty disturbing.

10:27.836 --> 10:28.962
Lucy: Tim.

10:31.506 --> 10:32.549
Police!

10:32.549 --> 10:33.675
Come out
from under the bed.

10:33.675 --> 10:35.135
Do it now.

10:35.135 --> 10:36.636
Come out
with your hands up.

10:36.636 --> 10:42.100
♪♪

10:42.100 --> 10:46.646
♪♪

10:46.646 --> 10:47.689
Holy crap.

10:50.942 --> 10:52.402
Tim: What is it?
It's ‐‐ It's a ‐‐

10:52.402 --> 10:54.070
A what?

10:54.070 --> 10:55.947
A mummy.

10:55.947 --> 10:56.906
In a suit.

10:56.906 --> 10:58.700
What?

10:58.700 --> 11:01.494
[ Clattering,
latex glove stretching ]

11:01.494 --> 11:08.001
♪♪

11:08.001 --> 11:09.252
Is that...

11:09.252 --> 11:10.086
It can't be.

11:10.086 --> 11:11.379
It looks like, uh ‐‐

11:11.379 --> 11:12.505
It was Charlie Chaplin.

11:12.505 --> 11:13.756
Charlie Chaplin's mummy.

11:13.756 --> 11:17.468
That was ‐‐ That was
Corey's greatest treasure.

11:17.468 --> 11:19.637
Lopez: And where exactly
did Corey obtain

11:19.637 --> 11:23.516
this mummified body,
Debbie?

11:23.516 --> 11:25.185
He stole it.

11:25.185 --> 11:26.227
<i>We</i> stole it.

11:26.227 --> 11:27.145
From who?

11:27.145 --> 11:29.147
From me. Yeah.

11:29.147 --> 11:31.316
No. I bought Charlie
at a secret auction

11:31.316 --> 11:33.484
I found out about from Nic.

11:33.484 --> 11:34.861
Cage. [ Clicks tongue ]

11:34.861 --> 11:37.113
I owe my entire career
to Charlie.

11:37.113 --> 11:40.074
He is my total inspiration.

11:40.074 --> 11:43.328
[ Laughing ]
I mean, that ‐‐ that tramp.

11:43.328 --> 11:46.080
Oh, my God. I wouldn't be
who I am today without him.

11:46.080 --> 11:47.457
You know?

11:47.457 --> 11:51.461
So when I found out
I could own him ‐‐

11:51.461 --> 11:54.255
Like, "Rainn, do you want to ‐‐
you want to own Charlie?"

11:54.255 --> 11:55.965
It was like
how could I say no?

11:55.965 --> 11:57.342
You know what I mean?

11:57.342 --> 11:59.928
So when I found out
that I was robbed,

11:59.928 --> 12:03.348
it's like I didn't care about my
vintage cowboy hat collection.

12:03.348 --> 12:04.891
You know what I mean?

12:04.891 --> 12:06.809
I don't care
about my solid gold retainer

12:06.809 --> 12:10.396
or Catherine the Great's
speculum,

12:10.396 --> 12:14.567
my SAG awards,
any of that stuff. No.

12:14.567 --> 12:19.489
I care about...losing
my best friend.

12:19.489 --> 12:20.990
Charlie.

12:20.990 --> 12:22.825
Harper: No. Of course
it wasn't Chaplin's body.

12:22.825 --> 12:24.994
So, apparently in the '70s,

12:24.994 --> 12:28.331
there was someone who actually
did steal his body,

12:28.331 --> 12:30.208
and they held it for ransom,

12:30.208 --> 12:31.542
but eventually it was returned.

12:31.542 --> 12:34.629
However, there are
conspiracy theories

12:34.629 --> 12:38.716
that the real body was sold
on the black market.

12:38.716 --> 12:41.970
So the mummy that we found
is just one of dozens

12:41.970 --> 12:46.432
of fake Chaplins
floating around.

12:46.432 --> 12:48.059
Celebrities are nuts.

12:48.059 --> 12:49.227
Interviewer: How did you feel
when you learned

12:49.227 --> 12:52.021
that Corey Harris
was behind the theft?

12:52.021 --> 12:55.817
Listen. I choose to live
in a realm of total positivity.

12:55.817 --> 12:58.611
I have nothing bad
to say about anyone,

12:58.611 --> 13:01.698
even a vain, talentless
skid mark like Corey.

13:01.698 --> 13:03.324
I've heard
that he targeted celebrities

13:03.324 --> 13:05.118
he felt had wronged him
in some way.

13:05.118 --> 13:06.661
Yeah. He ‐‐ He thought
the role of Backstrom

13:06.661 --> 13:08.496
should've gone to him.
[ Chuckles ]

13:08.496 --> 13:10.373
Anyway, so he sicced
his whole cult

13:10.373 --> 13:12.750
of acting students on me.
[ Exhales sharply ]

13:12.750 --> 13:15.545
And do you own
any other celebrity mummies?

13:15.545 --> 13:17.130
No comment.

13:18.006 --> 13:19.549
Tim: Before they became
a full‐blown cult,

13:19.549 --> 13:21.509
Corey turned his acting school
into a burglary ring

13:21.509 --> 13:22.635
that targeted celebrities.

13:22.635 --> 13:25.179
♪♪

13:25.179 --> 13:26.931
[ Rapping ] ♪ Ready or not,
I'mma come run up in your spot ♪

13:26.931 --> 13:28.057
♪ Like Kobe with every shot ♪

13:28.057 --> 13:29.309
♪ Cannot be stopped,
don't you go... ♪

13:29.309 --> 13:31.311
I caught a bunch of calls
back in 2018.

13:31.311 --> 13:32.687
That was before I was
on the job.

13:32.687 --> 13:35.064
We arrested a few people,
but no one would flip on Corey,

13:35.064 --> 13:36.566
so he got away with it.

13:36.566 --> 13:38.609
Yeah. Corey promised
his students everything ‐‐

13:38.609 --> 13:39.861
money, fame.

13:39.861 --> 13:41.237
But all he did
was insert himself

13:41.237 --> 13:42.530
farther and farther
into their lives.

13:42.530 --> 13:45.825
He made them think he could
control their destinies.

13:45.825 --> 13:47.285
I don't know.
Maybe it's because

13:47.285 --> 13:49.495
he didn't have any control
over his own.

13:49.495 --> 13:51.873
What's that saying?
Those who can't do teach?

13:51.873 --> 13:54.250
[ Chuckles ]

13:54.250 --> 13:55.668
You were literally
my teacher.

13:55.668 --> 13:58.796
What are you saying?

13:58.796 --> 14:00.465
[ Chuckles ]

14:00.465 --> 14:02.717
Aurora: My love! When I thrust
you with this knife,

14:02.717 --> 14:04.052
why didn't you cry?

14:04.052 --> 14:05.344
I've never seen a man die.

14:05.344 --> 14:06.804
Charlotte: No, no.
No, no, no, no!

14:06.804 --> 14:07.930
Enough. Stop.
Stop.

14:07.930 --> 14:09.557
G‐Get up right now.

14:09.557 --> 14:10.349
What is this?

14:10.349 --> 14:12.727
It's a‐a knife.
No.

14:12.727 --> 14:15.688
This is a vehicle
for the actor's soul.

14:15.688 --> 14:16.939
It must convey
all of your anger,

14:16.939 --> 14:18.483
all of your emotion.

14:18.483 --> 14:20.693
You just used this knife
to take a man's life,

14:20.693 --> 14:24.238
not chop onions in the back
of a fast‐food restaurant.

14:24.238 --> 14:26.324
[ Scoffs ]

14:26.324 --> 14:27.408
You know what I see
when I look at you?

14:27.408 --> 14:28.826
Hmm?
I see an amateur,

14:28.826 --> 14:30.369
a nobody going nowhere.

14:30.369 --> 14:32.997
Corey: Charlotte.
Charlotte, thank you.

14:35.416 --> 14:36.709
Aurora.

14:36.709 --> 14:39.295
[ Sobs ]

14:39.295 --> 14:41.798
What Charlotte means to say
is anyone can simply memorize

14:41.798 --> 14:43.841
or recite lines onstage.

14:43.841 --> 14:45.760
But only a few dare
to push themselves

14:45.760 --> 14:47.887
where their minds
won't allow them to go.

14:47.887 --> 14:49.931
That's what makes
a true actor.

14:49.931 --> 14:51.599
I can help you
get there.

14:51.599 --> 14:53.559
What do you say?

14:53.559 --> 14:54.685
Laurie: Hey!

14:54.685 --> 14:56.437
Turn that off!

14:56.437 --> 14:58.856
What did I tell you about
filming in my son's school?!

14:58.856 --> 15:00.650
[ Static hisses ]

15:00.650 --> 15:02.693
Corey was such a special boy.

15:02.693 --> 15:04.987
Everyone's best friend.

15:04.987 --> 15:06.739
Well, he didn't have
too many friends,

15:06.739 --> 15:08.783
come to think of it,
but that's because

15:08.783 --> 15:12.537
he was so dedicated
to his craft.

15:12.537 --> 15:15.081
He was a natural leading man,
even as a boy,

15:15.081 --> 15:19.210
and I knew he could succeed
at whatever he chose in life.

15:19.210 --> 15:21.295
And he and Charlotte together ‐‐

15:21.295 --> 15:23.464
You couldn't ask
for a better duo.

15:23.464 --> 15:25.341
A better duo
to brainwash people.

15:25.341 --> 15:27.218
Corey always made Charlotte
play the bad cop ‐‐

15:27.218 --> 15:28.553
no pun intended.

15:28.553 --> 15:30.388
So Corey could swoop in
and be the savior.

15:30.388 --> 15:32.431
Together they would brainwash
a student

15:32.431 --> 15:34.392
to the point where they would do
anything to please him.

15:34.392 --> 15:36.894
Yeah. And that's when he would
induct them into his Bling Ring,

15:36.894 --> 15:38.354
telling them
that the only way to get

15:38.354 --> 15:40.106
into the mind of a criminal
was to become one.

15:40.106 --> 15:41.941
He ruined people's lives.

15:41.941 --> 15:43.901
Interviewer:
Including someone you know.

15:43.901 --> 15:44.944
What?

15:44.944 --> 15:45.778
It's up here on the right.

15:45.778 --> 15:47.280
[ Knock on door ]

15:47.280 --> 15:48.823
Oh. Can I help you?

15:48.823 --> 15:50.283
Interviewer:
Sterling Freeman.

15:50.283 --> 15:51.784
Is it true that you were
once a student

15:51.784 --> 15:54.871
of notorious acting teacher
turned cult leader Corey Harris?

15:54.871 --> 15:57.123
What? No.
Okay. You can leave now,
thank y‐‐

15:57.123 --> 16:00.042
In fact, your real name
isn't Sterling Freeman, is it?

16:00.042 --> 16:02.044
It's Skipper Young,
and you participated

16:02.044 --> 16:04.297
in a ring
of celebrity burglaries in 2017

16:04.297 --> 16:05.756
at the direction
of Harris.

16:05.756 --> 16:07.758
Okay. What the hell is he
talking about?

16:07.758 --> 16:09.594
Your name is Skipper?

16:09.594 --> 16:11.929
[ Exhales deeply ]

16:11.929 --> 16:13.306
[ Australian accent ] How the
bloody hell did you find me?

16:13.306 --> 16:14.849
Whoa. Why are you talking
all British?

16:18.186 --> 16:22.064
So, I have a‐a bit of
a confession to make, Jackson.

16:24.567 --> 16:28.529
I'm not really
from Tampa.

16:28.529 --> 16:29.280
Get out. Get out!
[ Door slams ]

16:33.743 --> 16:36.245
Well, you have to understand
that when I first arrived

16:36.245 --> 16:36.996
in L. A. six years ago,
I was a nobody.

16:36.996 --> 16:39.707
Just a weird kid from Melbourne.

16:39.707 --> 16:42.710
I had never even been
to the States before.

16:42.710 --> 16:46.839
But all I knew was
I wanted to be a star.

16:46.839 --> 16:48.799
Interviewer: And tell us
how you first met Corey.

16:48.799 --> 16:50.218
I knew who he was,
of course.

16:50.218 --> 16:52.178
"Paul's Place" was big
in Australia.

16:52.178 --> 16:54.513
Corey was a real actor, and
so I just thought, "Why not?"

16:54.513 --> 16:58.226
And I went to one class...
and he hooked me.

16:58.226 --> 17:00.061
He believed nothing in
this business is given to you.

17:00.061 --> 17:01.687
Whatever you want in life,
you have to take it.

17:01.687 --> 17:03.105
He said the burglaries
would help us

17:03.105 --> 17:05.191
internalize that mind‐set.

17:05.191 --> 17:09.070
Corey wanted to help us
learn to conquer our fears...

17:09.070 --> 17:10.780
push our boundaries.

17:10.780 --> 17:12.740
And do you still believe
in Corey's teachings?

17:12.740 --> 17:14.825
No. No. Not at all.

17:14.825 --> 17:17.495
Alright?

17:17.495 --> 17:20.623
Well, we fell out
right before my arrest,

17:20.623 --> 17:22.124
and that's when things
were getting really weird.

17:22.124 --> 17:24.877
You know, over time, you could
tell he was getting delusional,

17:24.877 --> 17:26.754
talking about spirits,

17:26.754 --> 17:28.923
calling us ‐‐ his students ‐‐
"the Worthy,"

17:28.923 --> 17:31.300
calling himself
a prophet.

17:31.300 --> 17:34.220
Well, it got to a point where...

17:34.220 --> 17:36.013
I told myself one last run
with the crew

17:36.013 --> 17:38.849
and then I'd leave.

17:38.849 --> 17:39.809
Then I got caught.

17:43.271 --> 17:47.733
No, I was not aware
that my boyf‐‐

17:47.733 --> 17:49.610
Sterling ‐‐

17:49.610 --> 17:51.612
Skipper was a felon.

17:51.612 --> 17:53.406
Or Australian.

17:53.406 --> 17:55.866
Yes, yes, I'm aware
that cops are not permitted

17:55.866 --> 17:57.660
to fraternize with felons.

17:57.660 --> 18:00.037
Y‐‐ This is
an actual active matter,

18:00.037 --> 18:02.290
and I have no further comment
at this time.

18:02.290 --> 18:03.666
Interviewer: Officer West ‐‐
I said I have
no further comment.

18:03.666 --> 18:04.917
Thank you.

18:04.917 --> 18:06.544
Officer West,
come on back.

18:08.421 --> 18:09.547
Jackson: How could you
not tell me?

18:09.547 --> 18:11.007
Hey,
I am still Sterling.

18:11.007 --> 18:12.633
No,
y‐you're not Sterling!

18:12.633 --> 18:14.468
You're Skipper Young
or whoever the hell that is!

18:14.468 --> 18:15.678
No.

18:15.678 --> 18:17.805
After I was caught, I served
four months' probation

18:17.805 --> 18:20.057
and I changed my name.

18:20.057 --> 18:21.726
I'm different now.

18:24.687 --> 18:26.230
[ Whispering ] Please.

18:28.649 --> 18:31.736
That part of my life,
it's ‐‐ it's behind me.

18:34.822 --> 18:36.574
Do you believe me?

18:38.618 --> 18:40.703
I don't know.

18:40.703 --> 18:41.912
Jackson.

18:41.912 --> 18:44.373
[ Door opens, closes ]

18:47.752 --> 18:49.587
Nolan: Obviously, uh,
we knew that Sterl‐‐

18:49.587 --> 18:52.923
uh, Skipper had nothing to do
with it.

18:52.923 --> 18:56.761
He was in Prague shooting
a movie when it happened.

18:56.761 --> 18:58.429
So we still had a mystery
on our hands ‐‐

18:58.429 --> 19:01.182
a missing cult leader
and a bloody crime scene.

19:01.182 --> 19:04.602
That was when we became aware
of Corey's connection

19:04.602 --> 19:06.937
to someone who was
a lot more dangerous

19:06.937 --> 19:08.522
than a bunch of wannabe actors.

19:10.524 --> 19:12.985
The Southland Stalker
was a serial killer

19:12.985 --> 19:16.364
that terrorized L. A. County
starting in the fall of 2010.

19:16.364 --> 19:17.865
He had no type.

19:17.865 --> 19:20.534
He would hit single people,
couples,

19:20.534 --> 19:23.162
uh, even had a rampage
in a hotel once.

19:23.162 --> 19:24.914
Murdered three people
that night.

19:24.914 --> 19:26.749
But the Stalker got sloppy,

19:26.749 --> 19:28.167
and one of his victims escaped,

19:28.167 --> 19:29.377
went to a neighbor's home,

19:29.377 --> 19:32.380
and Dan Marcie was caught
in the surrounding area.

19:32.380 --> 19:33.506
There had always been rumors

19:33.506 --> 19:35.883
that the Stalker
didn't work alone,

19:35.883 --> 19:37.009
that he had an accomplice.

19:37.009 --> 19:39.261
But Marcie maintained in court

19:39.261 --> 19:41.430
that he did it all by himself ‐‐

19:41.430 --> 19:43.683
a performance
that we later learned

19:43.683 --> 19:45.476
he had a little help with.

19:45.476 --> 19:48.521
[ Buzzer sounds ]

19:48.521 --> 19:55.111
I met Corey in 2017
at one of his acting classes.

19:55.111 --> 19:58.864
I was looking for ways
to up my game,

19:58.864 --> 20:00.241
gain people's trust.

20:00.241 --> 20:01.409
Interviewer:
And why was that?

20:01.409 --> 20:03.077
So it'd be easier
to get my victims

20:03.077 --> 20:04.620
to come with me willingly.

20:06.539 --> 20:10.376
You see, for people like me ‐‐

20:10.376 --> 20:12.294
psychopaths ‐‐
there's a short circuit

20:12.294 --> 20:13.754
in the part of the brain
that feels empathy.

20:13.754 --> 20:15.756
At least that's
what the prison shrink tells me.

20:15.756 --> 20:20.511
Without that part, it makes it
difficult to relate to people,

20:20.511 --> 20:23.973
to convince them to trust you.

20:23.973 --> 20:25.683
I got tired of bashing people
over the head,

20:25.683 --> 20:27.643
dragging them to the car,
so I thought it'd be much easier

20:27.643 --> 20:30.146
if I could just charm them in
myself.

20:30.146 --> 20:31.939
So I asked Corey to help me.

20:31.939 --> 20:35.693
And did he teach you
how to fake empathy?

20:35.693 --> 20:38.487
Oh, yeah.

20:38.487 --> 20:42.616
It opened up a whole new realm
of possibilities for me...

20:42.616 --> 20:44.243
victim‐wise.

20:44.243 --> 20:45.411
There's a rumor
that Corey also helped you

20:45.411 --> 20:47.079
prepare for your trial,

20:47.079 --> 20:48.414
to better connect
with the jury.

20:48.414 --> 20:50.082
Yeah.

20:50.082 --> 20:51.292
Yeah, that's true.

21:12.354 --> 21:15.983
[ Chuckles ]

21:15.983 --> 21:19.695
I had the jury eating
out of the palm of my hand.

21:19.695 --> 21:21.280
[ Chain rattling ]

21:21.280 --> 21:23.574
But they still convicted you
of first‐degree murder.

21:23.574 --> 21:25.034
Yeah. Well, once they saw the
photos of her head in my fridge,

21:25.034 --> 21:26.535
it was kind of over for me.

21:26.535 --> 21:28.329
Dan Marcie was convicted
of murder

21:28.329 --> 21:30.498
months before Corey
went missing.

21:30.498 --> 21:33.042
But even though he wasn't
a suspect in the disappearance,

21:33.042 --> 21:36.128
his association with Corey
definitely made us

21:36.128 --> 21:39.215
take a closer look at who else
was taking those acting classes.

21:39.215 --> 21:41.509
And in the end,
it wasn't a student

21:41.509 --> 21:43.594
that gave us a break in the case
that we needed.

21:43.594 --> 21:45.763
It was Corey's old co‐star
and fellow teacher,

21:45.763 --> 21:46.806
Charlotte Luster.

21:46.806 --> 21:49.809
♪♪

21:49.809 --> 21:51.143
Well, no one had heard
from her

21:51.143 --> 21:52.436
since the day Corey
went missing,

21:52.436 --> 21:54.230
and we were about
to find out why.

21:54.230 --> 21:57.107
[ Jet engines humming ]

21:57.107 --> 22:02.738
♪♪

22:02.738 --> 22:04.657
Been parked here a week,

22:04.657 --> 22:07.201
and there's a really bad smell
coming from the trunk.

22:07.201 --> 22:08.744
Tim: Would you mind stepping
away from the vehicle?

22:08.744 --> 22:10.496
It belongs to a suspect
in a violent crime.

22:10.496 --> 22:16.919
♪♪

22:16.919 --> 22:18.671
[ Trunk opens ]

22:18.671 --> 22:22.675
♪♪

22:26.887 --> 22:29.139
Corey Harris
and Charlotte Luster.

22:29.139 --> 22:31.225
You played childhood sweethearts
for eight seasons

22:31.225 --> 22:32.518
on "Paul's Place,"

22:32.518 --> 22:36.021
and now I hear you've become
partners in real life.

22:36.021 --> 22:38.649
You know, Robin, when you
grow up with someone on TV,

22:38.649 --> 22:40.359
it just...

22:40.359 --> 22:42.319
it bonds you.
Mm.

22:42.319 --> 22:44.488
Charlotte was always
like family.

22:44.488 --> 22:45.739
And when she and Corey
started dating,

22:45.739 --> 22:48.909
I couldn't have been happier.

22:48.909 --> 22:51.412
I treated her
like my own daughter.

22:51.412 --> 22:54.498
And if I'm being frank,

22:54.498 --> 22:56.292
she was the luckiest girl
in the world

22:56.292 --> 22:59.920
to be able to date my son.
[ Chuckles ]

22:59.920 --> 23:03.716
Corey, it's no secret that you
struggled after the show ended.

23:03.716 --> 23:05.926
Drugs, alcohol,
even an arrest

23:05.926 --> 23:09.305
for indecent exposure
at an Emmy party.

23:09.305 --> 23:11.307
Oh, that was all
a misunderstanding.

23:11.307 --> 23:13.976
But what is true is that when
"Paul's Place" was canceled,

23:13.976 --> 23:17.313
I was a ‐‐
I was a mess, adrift.

23:17.313 --> 23:19.607
It was Charlotte
who brought me back.

23:19.607 --> 23:20.816
She saved me.

23:20.816 --> 23:23.569
♪♪

23:23.569 --> 23:25.529
News anchor: Breaking news ‐‐
Charlotte Luster,

23:25.529 --> 23:29.074
the former child star known for
the '90s sitcom "Paul's Place,"

23:29.074 --> 23:31.160
has been missing
since Sunday.

23:31.160 --> 23:33.662
She is the prime suspect
in the bloody disappearance

23:33.662 --> 23:35.581
of Corey Harris.

23:35.581 --> 23:37.499
Lucy: Even though we found
Charlotte's car at the airport,

23:37.499 --> 23:38.792
we couldn't find
any recent records

23:38.792 --> 23:40.294
of her boarding a flight
at LAX.

23:40.294 --> 23:41.587
Uh, Detective Harper and I
were dispatched

23:41.587 --> 23:43.964
to Charlotte's apartment
to begin a search,

23:43.964 --> 23:46.008
try to find some indication
of where she might've gone.

23:46.008 --> 23:47.509
Interviewer: And did you?
No.

23:47.509 --> 23:49.637
But we did find something
that shed some light.

23:49.637 --> 23:50.554
What was that?

23:50.554 --> 23:52.473
A screenplay.

23:52.473 --> 23:53.599
For a movie.

23:53.599 --> 23:55.225
It's L. A.
It's not the first time

23:55.225 --> 23:56.727
I've found a script
at a crime scene.

23:56.727 --> 23:58.062
I've only been on the job
for a year,

23:58.062 --> 23:59.939
and I've already
found three.

23:59.939 --> 24:01.565
Interviewer: Have either of you
ever written one?

24:01.565 --> 24:03.359
[ Scoffs ] God, no.

24:06.236 --> 24:07.738
It was for a class.

24:07.738 --> 24:09.740
It was the title
that caught everyone's eye ‐‐

24:09.740 --> 24:11.075
"The Worthy."
Aurora: ...the Worthy...

24:11.075 --> 24:12.993
...the Worthy...
...the Worthy.

24:12.993 --> 24:13.911
Same as Corey's cult.

24:13.911 --> 24:15.621
This script is...

24:15.621 --> 24:17.206
...500 pages long.

24:17.206 --> 24:20.209
So we assigned three
of our rookie officers

24:20.209 --> 24:22.336
the task of reading it.
[ Script thuds ]

24:22.336 --> 24:23.170
Interviewer: What did you think
of it?

24:23.170 --> 24:25.923
Look,
I'm no screenwriting expert,

24:25.923 --> 24:29.426
but I thought
it was, uh...dense.

24:29.426 --> 24:30.803
Convoluted.

24:30.803 --> 24:32.554
The worst thing
I have ever read.

24:32.554 --> 24:34.264
"Exterior, rooftop, day."

24:34.264 --> 24:36.392
"Aurora, 19,

24:36.392 --> 24:38.227
beautiful
but doesn't know it,

24:38.227 --> 24:40.187
speaks the prophecy aloud."

24:40.187 --> 24:42.314
"Heed ye
the Noon Star Harvesters,

24:42.314 --> 24:44.942
for they shall descend
from the heavens

24:44.942 --> 24:47.361
so the Worthy can ascend."

24:47.361 --> 24:49.822
"So sayeth
the Prophet Jedediah."

24:49.822 --> 24:52.074
"All hail Children
of the Stars."

24:52.074 --> 24:54.410
Group: All hail Children
of the Stars.

24:54.410 --> 24:55.619
Tim: Yep.

24:55.619 --> 24:58.288
He based his freakin' cult
off a bad sci‐fi script.

24:58.288 --> 25:00.124
That Charlotte wrote
with him.

25:00.124 --> 25:03.293
I've been a film producer
for like 25 years, okay?

25:03.293 --> 25:05.254
This is the strangest thing
I've ever seen.

25:05.254 --> 25:07.965
Well, second strangest.

25:07.965 --> 25:10.175
Anyway,
it was like five years ago,

25:10.175 --> 25:12.302
and I heard about this script
making the rounds.

25:12.302 --> 25:15.514
And listen. It's not uncommon
for actors to, you know,

25:15.514 --> 25:17.725
try their hand at writing
when the roles dry up, right?

25:17.725 --> 25:20.227
And P. S. ‐‐ everyone thinks
they got the next "Rocky."

25:20.227 --> 25:22.312
But a 500‐page space opera
written

25:22.312 --> 25:24.815
by two former child stars
raised a few eyebrows.

25:24.815 --> 25:26.400
I took the meeting.

25:26.400 --> 25:29.820
I mean, out of morbid curiosity
more than anything, right?

25:29.820 --> 25:33.365
It was...uncomfortable.

25:33.365 --> 25:34.867
And Charlotte,

25:34.867 --> 25:38.287
she seemed totally willing
to receive feedback, you know?

25:38.287 --> 25:42.207
Corey, he just flatly refused
to make any cuts to the script.

25:42.207 --> 25:45.127
I told them as politely
as I could.

25:45.127 --> 25:47.129
"It's a pass."

25:47.129 --> 25:48.297
Interviewer:
And then what happened?

25:48.297 --> 25:50.299
Well, then I forgot about it
for a long time.

25:50.299 --> 25:52.801
And then things got weird.

25:52.801 --> 25:54.762
Today, police rescued
five people

25:54.762 --> 25:56.680
from a Mid‐Wilshire rooftop.

25:56.680 --> 25:59.266
The group identified themselves
as members of "the Worthy"

25:59.266 --> 26:02.144
and were preparing
to commit ritual suicide

26:02.144 --> 26:04.021
based on the teachings
of their leader,

26:04.021 --> 26:06.482
known simply
as the Prophet Jedediah.

26:06.482 --> 26:08.525
You want to know why Corey
wasn't on that rooftop

26:08.525 --> 26:10.486
ready to jump
with the rest of his followers?

26:10.486 --> 26:12.071
Because he was filming it.

26:12.071 --> 26:14.031
Sheila: The day after
the missile alert,

26:14.031 --> 26:15.407
I get an e‐mail from Corey.

26:15.407 --> 26:19.161
The subject line ‐‐
"Proof of Concept."

26:19.161 --> 26:21.455
I...I couldn't believe
what I was seeing.

26:21.455 --> 26:24.333
Five people almost died

26:24.333 --> 26:25.667
because
some washed‐up narcissist

26:25.667 --> 26:27.169
thought that the world
he dreamed up

26:27.169 --> 26:29.046
in his screenplay
had become real.

26:29.046 --> 26:30.798
Along with the video,
Corey also sent Sheila

26:30.798 --> 26:32.007
a revised version
of his script.

26:32.007 --> 26:33.967
Yeah. W‐With Charlotte Luster's
name removed.

26:33.967 --> 26:35.260
He was trying
to cut her out ‐‐

26:35.260 --> 26:37.012
from the script, the cult,
and the money.

26:37.012 --> 26:46.271
♪♪

27:18.387 --> 27:21.306
Hell hath no fury
like a woman scorned, right?

27:21.306 --> 27:22.683
Cool.

27:22.683 --> 27:25.352
Way to trivialize
female anger.

27:25.352 --> 27:27.271
Hey,
I'm not trivializing.

27:27.271 --> 27:28.605
All sorts of crimes
are motivated

27:28.605 --> 27:29.815
by jealous ex‐partners.

27:29.815 --> 27:31.942
And how many of
those ex‐partners are men?

27:33.694 --> 27:35.988
Most.

27:35.988 --> 27:36.905
Interviewer: I heard
it was Officer Chen

27:36.905 --> 27:38.365
who broke the case
wide open.

27:38.365 --> 27:40.033
[ Chuckles ]
I d‐‐ I don't know

27:40.033 --> 27:41.827
if I'd describe it
quite that way.

27:41.827 --> 27:45.205
How <i>would</i> you describe it,
then?

27:45.205 --> 27:48.709
Her addiction to social media
finally paid off.

27:48.709 --> 27:50.669
T‐That is hurtful.

27:50.669 --> 27:52.296
I...[ Sighs ]

27:52.296 --> 27:54.131
Can you tell us
what happened?

27:54.131 --> 27:57.593
I was on my phone,
doing...research

27:57.593 --> 27:59.428
when I got a notification.
Ah.

27:59.428 --> 28:00.470
And ‐‐ You know what?

28:00.470 --> 28:01.889
I‐I still have the video
on my phone.

28:01.889 --> 28:04.057
Just let me...

28:04.057 --> 28:04.892
Look at that.

28:04.892 --> 28:07.561
[ Up‐tempo music playing ]

28:07.561 --> 28:08.937
That's ‐‐ Uh, that's ‐‐
Sorry.

28:08.937 --> 28:10.772
That's not what ‐‐
No.

28:10.772 --> 28:12.107
[ Down‐tempo music plays ]

28:12.107 --> 28:13.233
You are never gonna believe

28:13.233 --> 28:15.068
the celeb sighting
I just made

28:15.068 --> 28:17.696
during my Malibu
silent retreat.

28:17.696 --> 28:19.740
That's Corey Harris.

28:19.740 --> 28:21.074
He was alive.

28:26.163 --> 28:28.624
Harper: You have the right
to remain silent.

28:28.624 --> 28:31.251
Anything you say can be used
against you in a court of law.

28:31.251 --> 28:33.337
You have the right
to an attorney.

28:33.337 --> 28:37.799
If you cannot afford one,
one will be provided for you.

28:37.799 --> 28:39.468
Do you understand?

28:41.678 --> 28:43.931
Do you understand, sir?

28:46.058 --> 28:47.809
Corey?

28:47.809 --> 28:51.021
Uh, he took the "right to remain
silent" part real seriously.

28:51.021 --> 28:52.606
Very seriously.

28:52.606 --> 29:02.282
♪♪

29:02.282 --> 29:12.125
♪♪

29:12.125 --> 29:13.460
Interviewer: How long
did he stay quiet?

29:13.460 --> 29:15.003
Five and a half hours.

29:15.003 --> 29:18.215
♪♪

29:18.215 --> 29:20.926
[ Watch beeping ]

29:24.763 --> 29:27.307
[ Exhales deeply ]
Wow.

29:27.307 --> 29:29.851
That was invigorating.

29:29.851 --> 29:31.144
72 hours
of silence.

29:31.144 --> 29:33.563
You guys should try it.

29:33.563 --> 29:34.773
Now, what'd you want
to ask me?

29:34.773 --> 29:36.775
What a putz.

29:36.775 --> 29:40.404
So, Corey, while you were, uh,
playing your little quiet game,

29:40.404 --> 29:42.197
we were getting
the forensics report

29:42.197 --> 29:43.949
back from the lab.

29:43.949 --> 29:46.034
Do you care to guess
what it said?

29:46.034 --> 29:47.577
That I'm innocent.

29:47.577 --> 29:50.122
No. That the blood that we found
at your house

29:50.122 --> 29:52.582
and in Charlotte's car
belong to the same person.

29:52.582 --> 29:53.583
Who?

29:53.583 --> 29:55.127
Charlotte.

29:55.127 --> 29:56.378
[ Inhales, exhales deeply ]

29:56.378 --> 29:58.839
Oh, my God!

29:58.839 --> 30:01.174
That's horrible!
My ‐‐ My poor girl.

30:01.174 --> 30:02.634
[ Sobs ]

30:02.634 --> 30:04.845
Harper: Wow. You're right.
He <i>is</i> a good actor.

30:04.845 --> 30:05.721
Nolan: I told you.
Mm‐hmm.

30:05.721 --> 30:07.764
So what happened
to Charlotte?

30:07.764 --> 30:09.641
I have no idea.

30:09.641 --> 30:11.601
I haven't seen her
in weeks.

30:11.601 --> 30:13.061
And I've been at the silent
retreat since last Monday.

30:13.061 --> 30:14.688
I‐I'm sure
they have a record.

30:14.688 --> 30:16.356
Yeah. An employee
recalls checking you in

30:16.356 --> 30:18.400
at 10:00 a. m.
Sunday morning.

30:18.400 --> 30:20.152
Unfortunately, no one else
remembers seeing you

30:20.152 --> 30:22.237
until the welcome bonfire
that evening.

30:22.237 --> 30:25.490
That leaves an eight‐hour window
that is unaccounted for ‐‐

30:25.490 --> 30:27.576
plenty of time for you
to leave the retreat,

30:27.576 --> 30:31.413
go back home,
and kill Charlotte.

30:31.413 --> 30:34.041
Do you have any proof
of that?

30:34.041 --> 30:38.378
Of course not,
because I didn't do it.

30:38.378 --> 30:40.255
I could never hurt
another person.

30:40.255 --> 30:42.090
What about your followers,

30:42.090 --> 30:45.135
the ones you almost persuaded
to jump off a roof for you?

30:45.135 --> 30:46.845
For me?

30:46.845 --> 30:48.722
They were doing it
for themselves,

30:48.722 --> 30:50.599
for their own
enlightenment,

30:50.599 --> 30:53.393
so they could ascend
into a higher state of being.

30:53.393 --> 30:54.770
[ Sighs ]

30:54.770 --> 30:57.898
I wouldn't expect someone
as limited as you to understand.

30:57.898 --> 30:59.274
Is that what you call
the people

30:59.274 --> 31:01.068
who can see through
your little act?

31:01.068 --> 31:04.321
Was ‐‐
Was Charlotte limited?

31:04.321 --> 31:05.739
In some ways, yes.

31:05.739 --> 31:07.991
Is that
why you killed her?

31:07.991 --> 31:10.285
I think I need a lawyer.

31:10.285 --> 31:12.829
Because she saw
the real you.

31:12.829 --> 31:14.414
Because she had the power

31:14.414 --> 31:15.665
to send your house of cards
toppling.

31:17.542 --> 31:19.503
Lawyer.

31:19.503 --> 31:20.712
Wesley: I can't talk
about clients.

31:20.712 --> 31:22.255
I told you that
when you called yesterday.

31:22.255 --> 31:24.174
Interviewer:
Even given what happened?

31:24.174 --> 31:25.425
Yeah.

31:25.425 --> 31:26.551
Corey built
his whole empire

31:26.551 --> 31:28.136
on a script
he stole from Charlotte,

31:28.136 --> 31:29.387
and she was gonna
expose him.

31:29.387 --> 31:30.931
That sounds like motive
for murder to me.

31:30.931 --> 31:32.057
Hey,
speculate all you like.

31:32.057 --> 31:33.517
There was never
any evidence.

31:33.517 --> 31:34.518
There was video.

31:34.518 --> 31:36.311
Which did not show
my client.

31:36.311 --> 31:37.562
Now leave me alone.

31:37.562 --> 31:45.612
♪♪

31:45.612 --> 31:53.662
♪♪

31:53.662 --> 32:01.711
♪♪

32:01.711 --> 32:05.382
Nolan: Enter the "momager."

32:05.382 --> 32:06.925
Mom and manager.

32:06.925 --> 32:09.261
It's all a hybrid.

32:09.261 --> 32:10.595
I thought that was clever.

32:10.595 --> 32:12.222
Anyway, once we saw the footage

32:12.222 --> 32:13.974
of her tampering
with the evidence,

32:13.974 --> 32:15.642
it was clear to us
that Laurie Harris played

32:15.642 --> 32:19.271
at least some small
or, shall we say,

32:19.271 --> 32:22.357
behind‐the‐scenes role
in the crime.

32:22.357 --> 32:23.400
Interviewer:
I don't get it.

32:23.400 --> 32:25.360
I'm not gonna make
any more jokes.

32:25.360 --> 32:27.279
Harper: So, Mrs. Harris,
what happened to Charlotte?

32:27.279 --> 32:29.156
Last I heard,
she was flying to Cabo.

32:29.156 --> 32:33.994
So...soakin' up the sun,
sippin' on margaritas?

32:33.994 --> 32:37.164
Charlotte is not in Cabo,
Mrs. Harris.

32:37.164 --> 32:39.249
Was it Cancun?

32:39.249 --> 32:40.417
You drove her car
to the airport,

32:40.417 --> 32:41.918
and then you left it there
to make it look like

32:41.918 --> 32:43.461
she had left town.

32:43.461 --> 32:44.462
Oh. [ Snorts ]

32:44.462 --> 32:46.006
That?

32:46.006 --> 32:47.757
She asked me
to leave her car there.

32:47.757 --> 32:50.135
Really? That's weird,
because we found her blood

32:50.135 --> 32:51.970
at your son's house

32:51.970 --> 32:55.223
and then also in the trunk
of her car.

32:55.223 --> 32:58.351
And we also just found
what remains of her body

32:58.351 --> 32:59.978
dumped heartlessly

32:59.978 --> 33:03.648
20 miles
up Interstate 5.

33:03.648 --> 33:05.233
T‐‐ My God.

33:05.233 --> 33:10.238
That's...awful!

33:10.238 --> 33:13.909
Poor Charlotte.

33:13.909 --> 33:16.536
Clearly, Corey
did not get his acting talents

33:16.536 --> 33:17.579
from his mother.

33:17.579 --> 33:20.165
Seriously.
That wasn't even believable.

33:20.165 --> 33:23.501
But you have bigger problems
than your lack of acting chops.

33:23.501 --> 33:26.129
Charlotte's car
had GPS tracking.

33:26.129 --> 33:29.591
You should've disabled it
before you dumped her body.

33:29.591 --> 33:32.260
You can't prove I was anywhere
<i>but</i> the airport.

33:32.260 --> 33:33.720
Did you kill her,
Mrs. Harris,

33:33.720 --> 33:35.138
or were you just
cleaning up

33:35.138 --> 33:36.806
another one
of your son's messes?

33:36.806 --> 33:38.850
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

33:38.850 --> 33:41.228
I think Corey checked in
at the retreat

33:41.228 --> 33:43.188
and then he left
to go meet Charlotte.

33:43.188 --> 33:46.107
He killed her and called you
to clean it up.

33:46.107 --> 33:48.944
Then he went back
to his silent meditation

33:48.944 --> 33:51.154
while you dumped the body
of a woman you'd known

33:51.154 --> 33:54.699
since she was a child
like so much trash.

33:54.699 --> 33:58.536
♪♪

33:58.536 --> 34:03.166
Corey had nothing to do
with it.

34:03.166 --> 34:04.960
Are you sure?

34:04.960 --> 34:07.337
Yeah.

34:07.337 --> 34:11.049
I killed her
all by myself.

34:18.056 --> 34:19.766
Interviewer: Can you blame her
for trying to protect her son?

34:19.766 --> 34:21.184
Uh, yeah.

34:21.184 --> 34:22.519
She killed somebody.

34:22.519 --> 34:24.938
Sure. But if your son
had done something

34:24.938 --> 34:26.356
that would destroy
his life,

34:26.356 --> 34:27.732
wouldn't you try
and protect him,

34:27.732 --> 34:29.192
throw yourself
on the grenade?

34:30.986 --> 34:32.570
[ Inhales deeply ]

34:32.570 --> 34:36.533
Your job as a parent
is to protect your children

34:36.533 --> 34:38.660
as much as you can.

34:38.660 --> 34:42.038
But that also means
teaching them right from wrong.

34:42.038 --> 34:43.832
And there has
to be consequences.

34:46.459 --> 34:47.669
Doesn't mean you love them
any less.

34:47.669 --> 34:51.548
It just means...

34:51.548 --> 34:53.008
parenting is hard.

34:53.008 --> 34:54.259
Harper: His mom confessed.

34:54.259 --> 34:56.469
And Corey Harris passed
the polygraph,

34:56.469 --> 34:59.055
so we had to release him.

34:59.055 --> 35:00.640
Interviewer: Doesn't sound like
you believe he's innocent.

35:00.640 --> 35:03.727
My belief or lack thereof
is irrelevant.

35:03.727 --> 35:07.314
The decision to charge lies
solely with the D. A.'s office,

35:07.314 --> 35:10.984
and they didn't think
it was a case they could win.

35:10.984 --> 35:12.986
Does that
make you angry?

35:12.986 --> 35:15.614
No. I mean, a high‐profile case
like this

35:15.614 --> 35:18.366
and a guilty plea
ready to go?

35:18.366 --> 35:20.702
I wouldn't have charged him
either.

35:20.702 --> 35:23.413
That doesn't mean I think he
should've gotten away with it.

35:23.413 --> 35:25.749
Well, but he didn't actually
get away with it, did he?

35:25.749 --> 35:27.626
Well...[ Scoffs ]

35:27.626 --> 35:28.543
[ Switch clicks ]

35:28.543 --> 35:30.295
[ Chuckles ]

35:30.295 --> 35:32.213
Good evening, Worthy ones.

35:32.213 --> 35:34.424
Welcome to my evening sermon,

35:34.424 --> 35:39.387
streamed across
all my social platforms.

35:39.387 --> 35:40.639
[ Liquid slurping ]

35:40.639 --> 35:42.015
[ Sighs ]

35:42.015 --> 35:45.602
You know, we are so blessed.

35:45.602 --> 35:49.898
So blessed to shine in the light
of Our Saviors Above.

35:49.898 --> 35:51.274
You don't know the comfort
I've drawn

35:51.274 --> 35:53.318
knowing that one day soon,

35:53.318 --> 35:55.236
they will come
to lift us all up.

35:55.236 --> 35:56.237
[ Thud in distance ]

35:58.448 --> 36:00.075
Hello?

36:04.704 --> 36:05.955
Nobody's supposed to be here.

36:05.955 --> 36:08.958
Uh...where was I?

36:08.958 --> 36:10.960
Um...right.

36:10.960 --> 36:12.796
Our Saviors.

36:12.796 --> 36:14.714
They spoke to me last night.

36:14.714 --> 36:17.759
The stars seemed to part
as I was out in the night sky,

36:17.759 --> 36:22.472
and I could hear their voices
just as clear as you hear mine,

36:22.472 --> 36:23.431
and they said ‐‐

36:23.431 --> 36:25.767
[ Electricity humming ]

36:25.767 --> 36:27.102
What the hell?

36:27.102 --> 36:28.770
The electric bill's
on auto‐pay.

36:28.770 --> 36:31.481
[ Thud in distance ]

36:31.481 --> 36:34.901
Hello?

36:34.901 --> 36:36.695
Aurora Number 2, is that you?

36:36.695 --> 36:38.738
This isn't funny!

36:38.738 --> 36:40.365
Come on.

36:43.451 --> 36:44.744
Be right back.

37:00.260 --> 37:01.302
[ Thud in distance ]

37:01.302 --> 37:02.971
[ Corey screams,
glass breaking ]

37:09.644 --> 37:11.563
[ Breathing heavily ]
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

37:11.563 --> 37:13.565
[ Sobbing ]

37:13.565 --> 37:16.025
[ Door rattles, closes ]

37:16.025 --> 37:18.945
[ Grunting ]

37:18.945 --> 37:19.988
[ Chair thuds ]

37:19.988 --> 37:21.781
Aah! How is this so heavy?!

37:21.781 --> 37:22.866
[ Pounding on door ]

37:22.866 --> 37:24.659
[ Breathing heavily ]

37:24.659 --> 37:29.873
♪♪

37:29.873 --> 37:30.915
Oh, my God!

37:30.915 --> 37:32.625
Oh, no, no, no.

37:32.625 --> 37:35.503
[ Gasping ]

37:35.503 --> 37:38.423
Siri ‐‐ Siri, dial 911, please.

37:38.423 --> 37:42.218
Pick up. Pick up. Pick up.

37:42.218 --> 37:44.304
Operator: <i>911.</i>
<i>What's your emergency?</i>

37:44.304 --> 37:45.930
[ Whispering ] Help.
Someone's in my house.

37:45.930 --> 37:47.223
I'm in danger.

37:47.223 --> 37:49.267
I am the savior,
the Prophet Jedediah.

37:49.267 --> 37:50.727
I can't die.

37:50.727 --> 37:51.644
[ Gasping ]

37:51.644 --> 37:53.813
[ Doorknob rattling ]

37:53.813 --> 37:55.315
<i>Sir,</i>
<i>are you still there?</i>

37:55.315 --> 37:56.900
[ Pounding on door ]

37:56.900 --> 37:58.818
[ Sobbing ] Oh, no!

37:58.818 --> 38:00.069
[ Thud ]

38:00.069 --> 38:02.030
I'm scared!
I don't want to die!

38:02.030 --> 38:03.281
[ Door rattling ]

38:03.281 --> 38:05.241
[ Screaming ]

38:05.241 --> 38:07.410
[ Glass shattering ]

38:07.410 --> 38:14.083
♪♪

38:14.083 --> 38:15.502
Nolan: Police!
Don't move!

38:15.502 --> 38:17.045
Drop your weapon!

38:17.045 --> 38:18.129
[ Knife clatters ]
Hands on your head.

38:18.129 --> 38:19.923
Interlace your fingers.
Now!

38:19.923 --> 38:21.257
You got him?
Harper: Yeah.

38:21.257 --> 38:22.884
Don't move.

38:22.884 --> 38:25.804
[ Handcuffs rattling, clicking ]

38:25.804 --> 38:29.849
Give me your other hand.

38:29.849 --> 38:31.726
Ronald Sanchez.

38:31.726 --> 38:32.894
Harper:
Where's Corey Harris?

38:32.894 --> 38:35.480
Most of him's inside.

38:35.480 --> 38:37.148
Except his eyes.

38:37.148 --> 38:38.983
You just found those.

38:38.983 --> 38:40.360
Harper.

38:40.360 --> 38:41.528
You got to bag them
as evidence

38:41.528 --> 38:43.196
and we got to clear
the house.

38:43.196 --> 38:46.699
♪♪

38:46.699 --> 38:48.159
What happened here,
Ronald?

38:48.159 --> 38:49.786
My coming‐out party.

38:51.663 --> 38:54.040
Yeah. It turned out
the Southland Stalker

38:54.040 --> 38:55.834
had an accomplice after all,

38:55.834 --> 38:58.920
and he was pissed
that Corey convinced Dan

38:58.920 --> 39:01.130
to take all the credit
during his trial.

39:01.130 --> 39:02.465
I'm sorry.
Can I say "pissed"?

39:02.465 --> 39:03.967
Look, I know it's crazy.

39:03.967 --> 39:06.010
But, I mean, this dude's
a freakin' serial killer who ‐‐

39:06.010 --> 39:07.679
who puts eyes in his pocket.

39:07.679 --> 39:10.056
He's not exactly firing
on all cylinders.

39:10.056 --> 39:18.147
♪♪

39:18.147 --> 39:19.357
Control,
we got one in custody.

39:19.357 --> 39:22.485
Going back inside
to look for the homeowner.

39:22.485 --> 39:23.570
[ Door closes ]

39:23.570 --> 39:31.619
♪♪

39:31.619 --> 39:33.162
Ready?
Harper: Uh‐huh.

39:33.162 --> 39:34.664
[ Door opens, rattles ]

39:34.664 --> 39:39.752
♪♪

39:39.752 --> 39:44.799
♪♪

39:44.799 --> 39:47.010
Oh, no.

39:47.010 --> 39:48.177
[ Static hisses ]

39:48.177 --> 39:49.512
Control, we got a 187.

39:49.512 --> 39:53.516
Mobilize detectives,
a supervisor, and TID.

39:53.516 --> 39:54.934
I think...

39:54.934 --> 39:56.644
I think this thing
is still on.

39:56.644 --> 39:57.937
Lucy: It was.

39:57.937 --> 39:59.564
By the time Harper and Nolan
secured the scene,

39:59.564 --> 40:01.983
Corey's live stream
had 400,000 viewers.

40:01.983 --> 40:03.693
Okay. Look. The case
was definitely weird.

40:03.693 --> 40:04.736
But I mean, come on.

40:04.736 --> 40:06.112
All this?

40:06.112 --> 40:08.072
This feels
so exploitational.

40:08.072 --> 40:10.783
The low‐hanging fruit
of celebrity scandal and murder.

40:10.783 --> 40:12.368
You should be making
serious documentaries

40:12.368 --> 40:13.786
about things
that really matter.

40:13.786 --> 40:15.163
Interviewer: My last film
was about climate injustice

40:15.163 --> 40:16.372
in Puerto Rico.

40:16.372 --> 40:18.875
It won a BAFTA.

40:18.875 --> 40:20.335
Oh.

40:20.335 --> 40:22.670
Well, alright, then.

40:22.670 --> 40:25.381
I j‐‐ I just want to say
this has been so fascinating.

40:25.381 --> 40:28.134
I love true crime,
and to be in a documentary,

40:28.134 --> 40:29.886
it's just ‐‐
it's a dream come true.

40:29.886 --> 40:31.220
Thank you. Thank you.

40:31.220 --> 40:32.513
Thank you so much
for doing this.

40:32.513 --> 40:34.223
Yeah.

40:34.223 --> 40:35.975
You got ‐‐ You got something
in your hair.

40:35.975 --> 40:37.352
What?
It's kind of ‐‐

40:37.352 --> 40:38.186
Has it been there
the whole time?

40:38.186 --> 40:40.021
Yeah. It's pretty big.
Let's get out of here.

40:40.021 --> 40:41.564
I would tell you if you had
broccoli in your teeth, man.

40:41.564 --> 40:43.107
What the heck?
[ Sighs ]

40:43.107 --> 40:45.234
Interviewer: Were you surprised
that Ronald killed Corey?

40:45.234 --> 40:46.653
No, no. Not at all.

40:46.653 --> 40:48.571
Guy's out of his mind.

40:48.571 --> 40:50.531
He was always super jealous
of my fame too,

40:50.531 --> 40:53.534
so I guess he needed
to get some for himself.

40:53.534 --> 40:56.037
♪ But I can't say the same
for me ♪

40:56.037 --> 40:58.873
The eyes thing was a nice touch,
though, I will say.

40:58.873 --> 41:01.292
Do you have a takeaway
from this experience?

41:01.292 --> 41:04.212
Um, I'm honestly
still processing

41:04.212 --> 41:06.172
everything that happened.

41:06.172 --> 41:07.382
And have you talked
to Skipper?

41:07.382 --> 41:09.842
Who?

41:09.842 --> 41:13.429
Oh, um...no.

41:13.429 --> 41:15.390
No. We, uh...

41:15.390 --> 41:17.934
We've gone
our separate ways.

41:17.934 --> 41:20.019
♪ Still ready for
something more ♪

41:20.019 --> 41:21.354
Interviewer: Was this
your craziest case?

41:21.354 --> 41:22.730
Oh, yes.

41:22.730 --> 41:26.234
This was definitely the craziest
case I have ever worked.

41:26.234 --> 41:27.819
Oh, it's nowhere
near the craziest.

41:27.819 --> 41:29.445
Interviewer: Really?
Can you tell me more?

41:29.445 --> 41:30.488
No.

41:30.488 --> 41:32.573
Uh, we're done here.
I'm gonna go.

41:32.573 --> 41:34.325
Actually, I have
a few more questions

41:34.325 --> 41:35.910
if you had an extra minute
or two,

41:35.910 --> 41:37.453
Detective Harper.

41:37.453 --> 41:39.455
D‐D‐Detective Harper?

41:39.455 --> 41:42.500
♪ How can I afford to fall
in love? ♪

41:42.500 --> 41:49.716
♪♪

41:49.716 --> 41:57.015
♪♪

41:57.015 --> 41:59.058
[ Audience gasps, laughs ]

41:59.058 --> 42:01.310
Mmm!
Tastes good!

42:01.310 --> 42:02.937
[ Laughter, applause ]

42:02.937 --> 42:04.147
<i>You know what I want to be</i>
<i>when I grow up?</i>

42:04.147 --> 42:06.190
An ice cream sundae.

42:06.190 --> 42:07.483
[ Laughs ] Silly.

42:07.483 --> 42:10.069
You can't be an ice cream sundae
when you grow up.

42:10.069 --> 42:11.571
Then I never want
to grow up.

42:11.571 --> 42:15.366
[ Laughter, applause ]

42:15.366 --> 42:16.909
Still funny.

42:18.536 --> 42:19.287
Murderer.

42:27.712 --> 42:33.843
♪♪

